This 12&quot; disco single was released by Jeff Lynne right before ELO's &quot;Out Of The Blue&quot; LP. It's quite a snappy little disco number, with classic Jeff Lynne vocals. I suppose it's safe to assume that Jeff plays all the instruments. The single was a complete bomb and it is now hard to find. I found a sealed copy in the cutout bin many years ago. Here is a fresh transfer for your enjoyment.
The vinyl was transferred on a Sony PS-LX350H turntable with an AT-440MLa stylus into a Philips standalone CD Recorder and ripped to WAV with EAC. CoolEditPro was used for editing and mastering. EQ was adjusted and the volume was normalized to 98%. Pops and clicks were removed by hand. There was no noise reduction processing of any kind.

Transferred &amp; Mastered by Needledrop - March 2008

